op align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Senority or NBG</span><hr size=1> All I'm trying to say is spread out the loot.  May not sound far to you but to me it sounds fine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/utelkandoretelenesis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telkandore Telenesis</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(9/18/01 8:16:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Senority or NBG</span><hr size=1> Just as Lilwee said, Balorf, it's your guild's goals that matter.<br><br>If a guild seriously wants to clear all of ToV and other such places/mobs of that difficulty, they gotta outfit their best warrior first with the best gear and work on down, cause if they don't they just won't be able to take down the mobs they have to take down, or at least it'll be a long long time before they get proper people properly outfitted. Everyone still gets good items with this system, it just takes some extra time. This system is for those that have the goal to be among the elite of EQ. <br><br>If a guild just wants to have fun, however, and everyone get items, then it's /random and spread out the loot. This system is for those that have the goal of just having fun, and eventually getting some nice stuff.<br><br>There's really no argument here heh, as it depends solely on a guild's/person's primary goal.<br><br>Telkandore Telenesis<br>60 Warrior<br>The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorg